tspan.tspan: 200409: RNAseAlert kit: test 05 - Cas13 RNAse activity
Repeat of previous assay, with the following changes:
Increase concentration of guide RNAs to 2.5ul
Include benzonase nuclease + substrate as a positive control
Pre-incubate Cas13 + guide RNAs for 10 minutes at room temperature
Pipette target RNA with the substrate on the plate, start the reaction with master mix (buffer + water + Cas13 + guideRNA)
Cas13 protein 10x; 5ul of stock Cas13 (2mg/ml) diluted by adding 153ul of strorage buffer (SB)
Storage buffer for Cas13 (Kellner at al, NM, 2019)
substrate 2 tubes + 185ul of nuclease free water (Josie)
dilute 10x for the reaction to obtain 1E5/ul
prepare tube A and B, mix them, then pipette all on plate using dispensing pipette
Volumes in ul per well. For 4 rplicates multiply by 4 then by 1.15
Working in quadruplicates, pipet the replicates in the same rows.
Incubate at 37°C (in Varioscan) and measure for up to one hour (e.g. 36min).
Measure fluorescence every 2min, ex/em 490/520nm, read each well for 100ms with 10ul delay.
